        <abstract>
            <p>Has written to A. J. Gower.</p> 
<p>Sends more copies of <hi rend="italic">Queries about expression</hi>.</p>  
<p><hi rend="italic">Pall Mall Gazette</hi> article [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">6342</hi>] is monstrous to say religion did not attack science. Should scientific men ignore whole subject of religion?</p> 
            <p>Sends French journal with article on JDH and one (weak) by Agassiz on geographical distribution.</p> 
<p>M. J. Berkeley has sent his address [<hi rend="italic">Rep. BAAS</hi> 38 (1868): 83–7].</p> 
            <p>CD differs with JDH on Owen; could hardly bear to shake hands with him.</p>
            <p>Wallaces, Blyth, Jenner Weirs are coming to stay on Sunday.</p>
        </abstract>
